 Mandriva Linux Security Advisory                         MDVSA-2013:217
 http://www.mandriva.com/en/support/security/
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Package : spice
 Date    : August 23, 2013
 Affected: Business Server 1.0
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Problem Description:

 Updated spice packages fix security vulnerability:
 
 An user able to initiate spice connection to the guest could use a
 flaw in server/red_channel.c to crash the guest (CVE-2013-4130).
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:

 http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2013-4130
 http://advisories.mageia.org/MGASA-2013-0255.html
 _______________________________________________________________________

